caption: CC's Cafe is a GEM for EATS!  My family and I have been eating there for years.  Food has always been very FRESH.  The home cooked muffins and cookies and pastry are so good .. that I look forward to them. Check out the fish and the chicken too..YUM!   Enjoy!  And Say Hello to Oscar when you are there, as he is such a gentleman!
One of my preferred locations for tasty American food. The food was super appetizing. Really nothing but good experiences here. This place has a great design.
Amazing food always... staff is always very helpful... This place is a hidden gem...
Favorite neighborhood cafe!
the brunch was very good, the pancakes were extraordinary, even those who were natural and the manager was very nice
Get coffee drink a coffee good coffee

This restaurant is my first choice restaurant.  Of all restaurants I know I favor it most. I always suggests to my friends to go to visit this restaurant. when  I want to go to a good lunchon, this place comes right away to my mind. outstanding and all kinds of  food and a large menu.professional crew, and nice vibes. Also important, the expence is modest. I praise this place with pleasure.

Good

Great little local joint, their food is great and their service is just as good.  Was able to try out their lamb chops, burgers and omelette and club sandwich.  All of which were great.  They've recently renovated and the quality is still the same

Came in a busy Sunday morning and waited for a bit, but it’s worth waiting. I had the house egg wrap which is amazing. Staffs were friendly and efficient. Live this cafe and definitely will come back again.

We found this small place almost under Manhattan bridge and we definitely enjoyed it! Small place but warm, nice staff, good ambient, tasty food! We had the Mexican omelet and the Lumber jack breakfast, the pancakes are delicious! Coffee was good too. Again, friendly service, nice conversation. Good price too, very good!
The food and coffee was delicious. I can't remember the name of the sandwich, but the avocado and sprouts one was so good. Marcos was very kind!

Delightful atmosphere with free WiFi. Sandwiches made with fresh ingredients, homemade soup was absolutely delicious. Quality lunch for less than $10. Got a hot chocolate to go and they topped it off with a couple of spoonfuls of real chocolate chips!
Amazing! Quaint. Delicious. Also, had an adorable secret back patio.
Great food and service
Love this place!!! Breathtaking
Best quesadillas ever!!!!!
Beautiful place with delicious food. Go there!
9.21.19 - not bad coffee. A little light and slightly strong on the herbal flavor. Very welcoming staff and cute back patio area, but heavy with flies...
We had one of our best meals here. Quiet, sat by the fully open window and enjoyed some very tasty pork tacos. Highly reccommend!
Amazing. The owner is very personable and warm. The menu offerings showcase the talent of the chef and are reasonably priced. It is baffling this place is not constantly packed.

One of the hidden gems of Two Bridges neighborhood. CC's menu has delicious dishes from their soup (chipotle bean is divine) to their sandwiches (try the avocado, cheese, sprouts one) to their main dishes (my friend vouches for the crab cakes), this cafe is a great spot for some comfort food and casual ambiance.
Good food, amaizing service. Food was excellent and made to order, fresh ingredients. The staff was super friendly and fast. Amazing spot, can't believe I didn't find this place sooner.
I took the sandwich « le paysan » DELICIOUS I recommend
Large selection, neighborhoody. Treats customers with care.
Great convenience if you’re in the area looking for brunch. Don’t be in any rush.

(Translated by Google) Delicious, affordable and justified prices. Good products. We had salmon and half chicken: we enjoyed ourselves. The marinades are really good. The accompaniments are good and healthy (cooked vegetables). We were welcomed. I recommend the cheesecake !! A treat to finish the meal. And finally, they offer espresso, which can be hard to find in the US;).  (Original) Délicieux , prix abordables et justifiés. De bons produits. On a pris le saumon et le demi poulet : on s’est régalé. Les marinades sont vraiment bonnes. Les accompagnements sont bons et sains (légumes cuisinés). Nous avons été bien accueillis. Je vous recommande le cheesecake!! Un régal pour finir le repas. Et enfin, ils proposent des espresso, ce qui peut être difficile à trouver aux us ;).
Great food!
Amazing, great atmosphere. Me and my partner loved it for lunch. Try the burger and they're fresh cut fries. Thank you for everything.

Was not open at 7:15am, even though they advertised they open at 7. Locks on doors indicated they weren't opening any time soon!
I live nearby and come here often. Amazing food, nice staff...
Great place

Im not big at writing reviews but this time it feels totally right..I love pancakes and during my visiting in new York I had them almost every day for breakfast...so long story short..I ended up in this little bar/restaurant in chinatown I couldn't believe it..best pancakes ever!!! lighter fluffy and very tasty...everything was made from scratch and the chef and the waiter are also very friendly. Awesome!

(Translated by Google) The coffee was not the best, but the homemade pancakes were scrumptious as was the bagel!  (Original) El café no era el mejor, pero las tortitas hechas en casa estaban riquísimas al igual que el bagel!
Filming location of "LIMITLESS" season 1 #19

Made us pay in cash because they said credit card machine wasn't working. It was pouring rain out there. They should have had a backup method to get money from credit cards. Would have gotten 5 stars if it wasn't for this. Paypal and square have cheap card readers. Have one for backup.

(Translated by Google) Excellent and less expensive than the surroundings. Very well ! Happy hours until 7 p.m. Wrap (pictured) for $ 6. Friendly welcome.  (Original) Excellent et moins cher que les environs. Très bien ! Happy hours jusqu'à 19h. Wrap (sur la photo) pour 6$. Accueil sympa.
Love their cuban sandwich...a small place but just the right type of food.

The sides are... not American-sized. For $4.50 you get 3 little slices of bacon.  Tasty tho.
I had the Best chicken vegetable soup there!! Friendly people, fairly quiet place.
Food is soooo delicious 😋 you should try CC’s wrap 🔥and salad are awesome

Nice nook in Chinatown
The half chicken dish tasted great and the cheese cake was very good as well
AMAZING food at a relaxed and casual place. I’ll be back!

Very Good!
Nice quiet place n excellent food/wine n beer
Can’t believe it took me so long to come back here! Had the most delicious French toast on snowy Saturday morning & I’ve been thinking about it since.

Amazing food. Amazing service! Very cute decor. Been here twice now and the owner is super attentive and friendly. He also really knows his wines. This is definitely becoming my favorite spot in the neighborhood. Highly recommend!
Good food. Good service

Tomas the owner of this cafe catered our recent 150 guest wedding and he was awesome. The food was absolutely delicious, we had a 3 course dinner and appetizers during the cocktail hour. We had Butternut squash soup,  green salad with a vinegarette dressing and the pre-selected entrees varied. They were baby lamp chops, salmon, roasted chicken, Slow cooked pork  vegetarian dish. He was very easy to work with when helping select items for the menu. We would definitely work with him, he's a professional and no job is too small or big for him.
One of my favorite places to grab an American-style breakfast in the area.
nice place！！ go with GF every weekend~

Relaxed, small town vibe and always delicious. This is my neighborhood go-to for any meal of the day!
(Translated by Google) Very good place, good service I recommend it.  (Original) Muy buen lugar, buena atención se los recomiendo.
Chill place. Good simple food, great price.
Nice little spot for lunch, sort of out of the way. Food was really good.
Great food with a small town atmosphere. I love this place
Very good coffee and egg wraps!
Small spot, decent eats. Liked it.
Wine, beer, fresh pastry... honestly nothing not to like

"Oh the weather outside is frightful But the fire is so delightfulI ......" so the song goes  I have found my Niche for dining in Manhattan!!! I love this place .. tonight fantastic South American music and the best food .. I ate a perfectly prepared steak with grilled spinach and green salad .. a lovely warm, dark red wine and a very cute cheese cake and blueberry for desert.. for this "hard to please non-foodi" it's a winner .. the staff are the best !! ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️
Cozy and out of the way. Perfect place to relax and have a great lunch.
Great food and atmosphere
Great food, soups, and amazing and friendly people. Such wonderfulness!
Food and service was fantastic. If you're in the area would definitely recommend hitting this spot.
This place is amazing, I ate breakfast here every day of my trip. The coffee is really good, staff are very friendly and helpful.

What a welcoming place! I was traveling alone and stopped in for a glass of wine. I immediately connected with the owner, Tomas, and one of the regulars. Great conversation and wonderful company.  They made me feel like I was part of the neighborhood and I'll never forget them. Put this little place on your itinerary!
Quesadillas were spectacular
This is my nearest experience ever I had, they are very caring and friendly relation wise
I'm amazed at the care and attention that the staff showed to our order: cappuccino and hummus. Both were made fresh and absolutely fantastic! I cannot recommend enough!
Thomas is a wonderful man with a large heart support the fashion & life he has brought to this neighborhood !!!

Absolutely my top recommendation! I had food there very often when I was on NYC. It's a small cafe with a great chef and a cozy atmosphere. Menu can be different everyday, but all tasty! I recommended it to my friends from China, Spain, France, Finland...they  all loved it!
Great atmosphere and friendly staff. Just a little over priced for what you get and is a good walk from the train.
This is a tucked away gem that is greatly welcomed in the neighborhood. Friendly atmosphere and great food, either for brunch or for dinner, you won't be disappointed.

Love the place! So excited that there was finally a chance to get coffee in the strictly tea zone of the downtown. Little did I imagine that it would be the best coffee Anywhere in downtown, or possible the Rest of town. Seriously - try their mocha late! It will make you cry! The food is just as good. And judging by the consistent business and cheerful atmosphere - I am not the only one who thinks that.  The staff is and the owner are friendly and clearly enjoy doing what they do - which, as we know is an easy recipe for success.  Great job guys!  So glad you are here!
